meta.description: THE LEGEND - What each field code means and what it creates

type_definitions.entity: Standalone entity that creates a node (person, company, email, etc.)
type_definitions.attribute: Metadata that attaches to a parent node
type_definitions.dataset: Structured data that creates nodes with edges to parent
type_definitions.graph: Creates multiple edges between entities (identity graphs)

creates_values.node: Creates a standalone node in the graph
creates_values.metadata: Attaches as properties to parent node
creates_values.edges: Creates relationship edges between existing nodes

meta.eyed_codes_description: Codes 187-195 are EYE-D OSINT outputs (breaches, social profiles, identity graph)
meta.alldom_codes_description: Codes 191-214 are ALLDOM/LINKLATER domain intelligence outputs
meta.gleif_codes_description: Codes 420-433 are GLEIF-specific (LEI, BIC, ownership structure)
meta.macro_codes_description: Codes 500+ are reserved for macro-specific outputs
meta.nexus_codes_description: Codes 600+ are for reified NEXUS relationship nodes
meta.id_decoder_codes_description: Codes 700-708 are ID_DECODER outputs (DOB, gender, jurisdiction from IDs)
meta.socialite_codes_description: Codes 709-719 are SOCIALITE outputs (profiles, posts, photos, logs, FB IDs, maiden names)
